The problem being that you waited until TWC was in force at the gate before you clicked over.  You had a lot of time previously to move in if you needed to, but it sounds like you didn't because of an AFK cleric who died.  If you required this cleric to kill Seru, then you should have waited for him before you moved forward, and not moved ahead rapidly to try and give an impression of first-in-force when in fact you weren't ready.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>&quot;My personal view is, TWC was not in the Lord Seru building. They were killing house masters. Lord Seru was not being moved on so we made him our target. Similar to ToV for example. If Guild A is killing Telkenor, and Guild B decides to make LTK their target and moves to them, In my opinion it would be silly of Guild A to say they were FIF for LTK because they were in the zone&quot;<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
The problem here is that by porting in, you had set the precedent that you would not considering first-in-force simply being here - that it would require to actually be killing Seru.  There is little difference between having 45 people in zone out of Seru building and having 45 people in the Seru building who are not ready to engage.  So until the point when Seru is actually engaged, both guilds can lay equal claim to him.<br>
<br>
Granted, it is very diffiicult for me to comment on whether ToN had enough clerics without this dead one, as the entire force was anonymous.  Since you had to wait on him, I am assuming this is so.  If we have 80 people ready to engage Emperor, and no enchanters or bards, then we are likewise not ready.<br>
